{"triple_norm": ["itachi", "be a member of", "theakatsuki"], "true_link": {"object": "NULL", "subject": "/m/02p8p45"}, "src_sentences": ["Itachi be a member of the Akatsuki", "Itachi is a member of the Akatsuki, and is signified with this via his cloak, the black and red cloud pattern on it&apos;s hem, and purple finger nail polish, which all members use to identify themselves. He&apos;s partnered with Kisame Hoshigaki within the Akatsuki, also known as the chakra shark.", "Itachi&apos;s first appearance in the manga and series is shortly after the Chuunin Exams arc and when the Third Hokage passes away. Before the search for Tsunade with Naruto and Jiraiya begins, Itachi appears in Konoha in disguise with his partner from the Akatsuki. After getting some tea from a local chop in Konoha, he was unable to escape the notice of Kurenai and Asuma, who had just then passed by Kakashi.", "After his gen jutsu had been deactivated, it was noted that Itachi&apos;s head began to throb. Before the Akatsuki\u00a0 duo were about to finish off their remaining opponents, Maito Gai appeared. Kisame was willing to fight them still, but Itachi noted that they had only come here for one purpose, and that was not to fight a war against Konoha. The two left and they tracked down Naruto in his hotel room that he had just recently been staying at with Jiraiya, the Toad Sage whom was also noted as one of the legendary Sannin. After they got him out of the picture through his biggest weakness (women), they made their way to where the Kyuubi was, sealed inside Uzumaki Naruto&apos;s stomach.", "Itachi, somewhere along the line, after killing the Uchiha Clan, joined the Akatsuki organization. The Akatsuki&apos;s (Meaning &quot;Dawn&quot;) ultimate goal, as stated by Pein, its leader, was to make peace with all the nations through brutal force. Orochimaru in the Akatsuki", "Their main goal was to capture all of the biju (meaning, the beasts similar to the one that Naruto had sealed in his body) and then extract their power to be placed inside of a large faced statue with it&apos;s hands prying through the ground, each finger representing the Akatsuki member who wore the ring of the finger they stood on. Itachi&apos;s ring is located on his right middle finger, and also bears the other Akatsuki trademark of purple finger nail polish. The one other obvious trademark for the group is the large black over coats with the red cloud pattern across them.", "When Orochimaru joined the Akatsuki, he had originally only intended to take Itachi&apos;s body, and was partnered with Sasori. Upon realization that Itachi was much stronger than he, he left the organization, but not before having his right hand claimed by Itachi, and severed. Orochimaru&apos;s flash back of the fight during his final battle with Sasuke showed that he was indeed less powerful than Itachi, being beaten once stared down by the Uchiha slayer. As he walked up the steps to Itachi, he found that he was paralyzed upon eye contact, Deidara, the terrorist turned Akatsuki member by Itachi", "Another event occurring in the Akatsuki before appearing fully in the series were the subsequent and violent events forcing Deidara into the Akatsuki. During Deidara&apos;s flash backs whilst fighting Sasuke, it is shown that Itachi, with Sasori and Kisame (after Orochimaru&apos;s defection) had met with Deidara while he was still a terrorist. He was to be the replacement for Sasori&apos;s now long gone partner. After being told who he was by Kisame, he questioned who they were and how they knew of his profile. After Itachi asked him what his reason for all the multiple terrorist attacks was, he simply proclaimed sarcastically that he never had a reason, nor needed one.", "Shortly after that he began to monologue on how he saw his explosions as works of art, and should be treated as such, to which Sasori muttered &quot;How long is this guy going to drone on....&quot;, to which Itachi simply said &quot;Who knows&quot;, and did the only thing they saw fit to silence him, which was challenging him to a fight. Itachi told him that if he beat him, he would join them in the Akatsuki after this. Deidara simply smirked, and made the mistake that everyone makes when fighting Itachi very quickly: making eye contact with him. The fight lasted for a few seconds, with Itachi seemingly be blasted up against a wall and then surrounded by Deidara&apos;s creations of explosive magnitude. Before attempting to blow Itachi to pieces, Itachi told him to take a close look at himself first, only to see that he had in fact attached his own creation to himself, fallen into a gen jutsu from the very beginning of the fight. The Power of his Sharingan", "Itachi&apos;s first appearance in Naruto: Shippuden is during the Gaara retrieval/extraction arc. On Naruto&apos;s way to the Akatsuki hide out with Sakura, Chiyo, and Kakashi, Itachi appeared to block their path. Kakashi tells Naruto to watch out for Itachi&apos;s powerful genjutsu before he tries too do anything in the fight, and Kakashi would distract him. While he said this, Naruto quickly remembered that he had indeed been taught by Jiraiya how to break and counter gen jutsu, but he never wanted anything to do with it. In fact, he ignored the entire idea and thought it was a stupid concept from the beginning. Jiraiya told him that he either had to sever his chakra flow from being poisoned by the illusion, or someone else had to touch him momentarily.\u00a0 Itachi told him that they did not have too much to worry about, as he would not, or more accurately, could not, use the Mangyekou Sharingan at that time. Naruto sent multiple shadow clones to strike him, all of them being destroyed easily. Itachi&apos;s crow doppelgangers were enough to suffice every blow that Naruto dished out, eventually trapping him into an illusion of his own, with Naruto thinking about all of his friends he was failing to save, or had failed to be a part of."], "triple": ["I